601
68:00.774 --> 68:07.500
The third lesson introduced
the quantum circuit model of computation, and in the fourth lesson, we took a look at three important examples

602
68:07.500 --> 68:11.340
that illustrate things we
can do with entanglement.

603
68:11.340 --> 68:17.910
Along the way, we saw some very important mathematical concepts,
including tensor products and inner products, and we observed

604
68:17.910 --> 68:22.290
some fundamental limitations
of quantum information.

605
68:22.290 --> 68:28.410
I hope you'll join me for
the next unit of the series, which will be on quantum algorithms, where we'll focus on the question

606
68:28.410 --> 68:32.880
of what computational advantages
quantum information offers.

607
68:32.880 --> 68:33.873
Goodbye until then.
